      • DEFAULT_VALUE

        static final String DEFAULT_VALUE
        This attribute is used to specify an initial value for the property when its getter method returns null. There are two possible situations
        1. Object specified for default value implements DefaultValue interface. In this case clone() method is used to obtain new instance for the property value.
        2. Object does not implement DefaultValue interface. In this case the value is simply used and it is responsibility of developer to ensure that it doesn't harm (for example mark property as read-only)
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • HELP_ID

        static final String HELP_ID
        This attribute is used a context help for the property. It can be some identifier of help resource as well as help message itself
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SIMPLE

        static final String SIMPLE
        This attribute is used to disable recursive introspection of some properties. Normally introspection is applied to all non-promitive properties to find out whether they are itself Beans.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • NO_RECURSION_CHECK

        static final String NO_RECURSION_CHECK
        This flag is caused by classes like java.awt.Dimension which contain property of the type java.awt.Dimension thus causing endless loop while recursively introspecting beans. Normally we suppress recursion but in some situations this screens out required properties. In such situation the developer can use this flag to aviod recusrion suppresion, but he may be required to write BeanInfo for the class in this case.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CAN_BE_NULL

        static final String CAN_BE_NULL
        This attribute is used to specify the property can be null
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SUBSTITUTE_BY_CHILD

        static final String SUBSTITUTE_BY_CHILD
        This attribute is used for composite properties when they contain the only visible child property. If this attribute is specified parent peoprty wil be replaced by child
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • READ_ONLY

        static final String READ_ONLY

      • CHILD_READ_ONLY

        static final String CHILD_READ_ONLY
        This flag indicates that array items are read only and can not be edited. This attribute usefull when you would like to edit array as whole by special editor.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • ORDER

        static final String ORDER
        This attrubute allows passing the order in which properties were added in using BeanInfoEx interface. This attribute can be extracted by visualization UI and used to display properties in order. The properties returned by BeanInfoEx.getPropertyDescriptors() method are not used passed through by Introspector - they used to create intermediate informant BeanInfo that is passed to the application. That's why this attribute is useful.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • COMPOSITE_EDITOR_PROPERTY_LIST

        static final String COMPOSITE_EDITOR_PROPERTY_LIST
        List of property names for composite editor.

        Semicolon is used as property names delimiter.

        Nested subproperties can be used.

        Examples:

        • "color;width;stroke"
        • "pen/color;pen/width;brush/stroke"
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
        PENDING:
        examples and comment

      • COMPOSITE_EDITOR_LAYOUT_MANAGER

        static final String COMPOSITE_EDITOR_LAYOUT_MANAGER
        Layout manager to arrange property renderers/editors inside the composite.

        Currently meaningful layout managers are only: GridLayout and FlowLayout.
